track_notes: Hiked along sandy wash to Inner Pasture, then took the SW ridge up to the summit. I left the wash about 500 feet too early, probably would be easier to stick with it a bit longer to avoid going between the 2 little hills. Took a steeper NW slope on the way down. Nice views N to the Vallecito Mtns and W down into Inner Pasture and the Sawtooth Mtns.
track_title: Nice desert hike via wash and XC

track_notes: NOT RECOMMENDED GOING DOWN THE NE RIDGE AS IT INVOLVES A LOT OF BOULDERS, CHOLLA, AND STEEP AREAS. BETTER TO COME BACK DOWN THE BACKSIDE VIA THE SW RIDGE AND TAKING THE SAND WASH BACK TO THE START.
track_title: LOOP UP VIA WASH AND DOWN VIA NE RIDGE

track_notes:
Took a slightly different route up this time, attempting to find the WWII plane wreck. This route follows a drainage up most of the way and is a bit more direct. It was pleasant enough that I basically followed the same route on the way down.

What remains of the wreck site is around 375 vertical feet below the summit.
